<br />
<br />The 16-byte header is pretty cramped anyways, there's over 500 bytes of room for the future with the using the trainer for info idea I mentioned in the other thread.  Since it'll inherit NES 2.0's extensions for good emulation, all that extra space could be used for the nice-to-have-but-not-absolutely-necessary things.</div>

